article.description: Khalil Shabazz had 15 points off the bench to lift San Francisco to a 101-50 win over Sonoma State on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Shabazz lifts San Francisco past Sonoma State 101-50
article.linkText: Shabazz lifts San Francisco past Sonoma State 101-50
article.story: SAN FRANCISCO -- Khalil Shabazz had 15 points off the bench to lift San Francisco to a 101-50 win over Sonoma State on Tuesday night. Charles Minlend had 15 points for San Francisco. Trevante Anderson added 12 points. Remu Raitanen had 11 points for the hosts. Isaac Davidson had 11 points for the Seawolves. Michael Smith added 10 points. Kenny Olsem had seven rebounds. San Francisco takes on Princeton at home on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
